tsh_module module¶

tsh_module.create_patient(firstname, lastname, age, gender, tsh_data)¶

This function creates a patient object.

Parameters:
  • firstname – string of patient’s first name
  • lastname – string of patient’s last name
  • age – string of patient’s age
  • gender – string of patient’s gender (male or female)
  • tsh_data – list of strings of various tsh data from the patient
Returns:

patient object with each parameter as a property
tsh_module.declare_result(patient)¶

This function outputs whether the patient has hyper/hypothyroidism or not.

Parameters:patient – patient object containing various properties
Returns:output string of diagnosis
tsh_module.file_output(patient)¶

This function outputs into a json the patient information.

Parameters:patient – patient object containing various properties
tsh_module.load_patient_data()¶

This function takes in all the patient data from a test_data.txt file.
